# LungLens Cursor Rules

## Scope
- Always apply these rules for this repository.

## Required Workflow Before Editing
1. Scan existing files involved in the request (imports, endpoints, types, UI flow).
2. Compare current behavior to architecture requirements.
3. Report: aligned, misaligned, and missing items.
4. Make minimal adjustments (prefer adapters/mappers over rewrites).
5. If a behavior looks intentional but conflicts with notes, ask before changing.

## Golden Constraints
- Frontend never runs ML inference and never imports ML runtimes.
- Frontend never preprocesses images to tensors; send raw files only.
- Backend owns preprocessing, inference, and LLM report synthesis.
- Frontend must not call OpenAI directly.
- Keep backend API secrets server-side only (no `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for keys).
- Always enforce gate-driven flow: only show clinical questionnaire when required.
- Always keep medical disclaimer visible in results-related experiences.

## Integration Rules
- Browser talks to Next API route first; route handles backend forwarding and auth header.
- Keep compatibility mapping when backend payload naming differs (`gate_result` vs `gate`, `requires_clinical_qa` vs `requires_questionnaire`).
- Validate incoming backend payload shape before returning success to client.

## Warm-Up Rule
- Trigger silent fire-and-forget backend health warm-up early in session.
- Warm-up must not block UI and must not surface warm-up errors to users.

## Documentation Rules
- Keep README/env var names consistent with executable code.
- Do not claim in-browser inference when production flow is backend inference.
